benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts - Retrieve an account by external key

covered: Valid Request: Verified successful retrieval of an account by externalKey under multiple parameter configurations (default, accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA, audit).
Not found/Empty data: Not-found (404) and empty-database cases tested (TC06, TC17).
Query Parameters Validation: Comprehensive coverage of externalKey and boolean/audit parameters; includes valid combos and invalid inputs (TC07–TC12, TC14, TC15, TC16, TC18, TC19).
Authorization: Tests for missing and invalid authentication tokens (TC11, TC12).
Error Handling and Reliability: Service unavailability (TC13), inconsistent data (TC24), and timeout scenario (TC25) covered.
Security: Injection and XSS test cases (TC14, TC15).
Performance: Baseline response time (TC20) and peak-load concurrency (TC21) and timeout (TC25).
Edge Cases and Compatibility: 255-character boundary (TC18) and 256-character exceed (TC19); extra parameters ignored (TC16); legacy compatibility (TC23).
Regression and Compatibility: Legacy client behavior (TC23) and regression coverage for problematic keys (TC22).
gaps: Pagination: Not applicable for single-resource endpoint; no list pagination tests needed, but no tests covering list pagination if such an endpoint exists.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or conditional requests (304).
Rate Limiting: No explicit rate-limiting tests; only concurrency tests rather than throttling.
Internal Server Error: No path to trigger 500 Internal Server Error.
Forbidden Access: No 403 Forbidden scenario for authenticated-but-not-authorized users.
Blank ExternalKey Input: No test for empty string externalKey value (i.e., externalKey="").
Content Negotiation: No tests varying Accept/Content-Type headers.
recommendations: Add explicit rate-limiting tests (429) to validate throttling behavior under high request rates.
Add 403 Forbidden test to cover authenticated-but-not-authorized scenarios.
Add tests that can trigger 500 Internal Server Error to validate server-side error handling.
Add caching tests (ETag/Cache-Control) including 304 Not Modified behavior.
Add test for empty string externalKey to cover blank input validation.
Add Accept header variations / content negotiation tests to ensure JSON responses with correct headers.
